<section id="tasks_importing_core_schemas_files">
	<title>Importing core schemas files</title>
	<para>
		To import core schemas files choose one of the following
		options:
		<itemizedlist spacing="normal" mark="bullet">
			<listitem>
				In the Schema view, choose
				<emphasis role="strong">
					Import >
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata scale="50"
							fileref="images/icons_schemas-import.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>
					Core schemas file(s)
				</emphasis>
				from the context menu.
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				In the Workbench menu bar select
				<emphasis role="strong">File > Import...</emphasis>
				and choose
				<emphasis role="strong">
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata scale="50"
							fileref="images/icons_schemas-import.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>
					Core schemas file(s)
				</emphasis>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</para>
	<para>The following wizard appears:</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata scale="50"
						fileref="images/tasks_import-core-schemas-wizard.png"
						format="PNG" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>
		Check each schema file you want to import and click on the
		<emphasis role="strong">Finish</emphasis>
		button.
	</para>
</section>
